<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="lgisaacs" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd" status="Needs Review">
  <title translate="true">Performance Levels</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Performance Levels</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Header 2" style="text-align:right;"><link displaytype="image" src="New_Back_Arrow_icon.gif" type="topiclink" href="Support"></link><text styleclass="Header 2" style="font-size:8pt;" translate="true"> </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Support" styleclass="Answer" style="font-size:8pt;" translate="true">Return to Support Menu</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab/><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can new performance level sets be added?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">In order to add a Performance Level Set, follow these steps.  </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">New Performance Level Sets can be added by higher end users only</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"></para>
          <list id="41" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Performance</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Levels</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> Icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Choose a </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Year</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> from he drop down and enter a </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Name</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Add</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Set</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">The newly added Performance Level Set will display.  Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Set Levels</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> under the Levels column.  One level will be added by default, click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Add</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Level</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> to add more.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Enter in the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Level Name, Abbreviation, Min Score, Max Score</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Color</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> for each of your levels.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Once a performance level set is added to the system it is available for use on tests.</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">  </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">All assessments will still default to the DistrictDefault performance set and must be manually changed if you desire to use the new one.  Follow the steps in &quot;Is it possible to have assessment use different performance level sets&quot; FAQ for details on how to change the performance level set for an assessment.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab/><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can existing performance level sets be edited?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, existing performance levels can be edited.  In order to edit a performance level follow these steps.  </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Only higher end users can edit performance level sets.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="39" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Performance</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Levels</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> Icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">year</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Name</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> if known</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Performance</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Level</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Sets</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Set Levels Icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> under the Levels column</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Make the desired changes to the Performance Level Set levels.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">If the District Default performance level set is edited it will reflect the changes on ALL assessments within your system.  Please exercise caution when editing Performance Level Sets due to the impact it will have on reporting.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab/><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Is it possible to have assessments use different performance level sets?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, it is possible to have different assessments use different performance level sets.  In order to do this you will need to manually set the performance level set you want the assessment to adhere to, by default, all assessments are tied to the District Defaults performance level set.  You must have custom added performance level sets in order to change the set on the assessment.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Here are some steps to change the performance level set on an assessment:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"></para>
          <list id="52" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Navigate to the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">profile</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> of an &quot;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">unproofed</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&quot; assessment (District or Classroom) by using the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icons</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> for </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">District</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Classroom</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> under the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Assessment</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> button.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">On the profile page locate the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Scoring</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> section and the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Performance Level Set</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> drop down</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Use this drop down to change the performance level set for the assessment</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">The Performance Level Set for an assessment cannot be changed after a test is proofed.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
